		<h2> Seek </h2>
		<p> Released April 2017 </p>
		<div class="col-md-3">
			<img class="img-responsive" src="https://yhwhapparel.files.wordpress.com/2017/04/seek27-e1492903081150.png"/>
		</div>
	  <div class="col-md-9" id="seek-desc">
			<input type="checkbox" class="read-more-state" id="post-1" />
			<span class="read-more-wrap">
				<p> To seek. </p>
		    <p> Is to search after. </p>
			  <p> When the waves seem to be rising faster. When our heart seems tossed around.
					When we feel like we keep hitting the same wall over and over again. When there’s no
					improvement. In him. In her. In us. It leaves us tired and weary, beaten down. </p>
		   	<p> But in times like this, we MUST remind ourselves of His promises. Even if our
					mind can recite it, our heart may not truly believe it. But by praying and declaring
					His promises for us, we are speaking TRUTH over ourselves, so that darkness and hopelessness
					will not overcome us. </p>
				<span class="read-more-target">
					<p> It’s tough. There’s no denying it. Things are jagged, crooked, broken, sharp.
						We get hurt, exhausted, frustrated. But what do we do when we keep getting knocked down? </p>
					<p> We must SEEK His presence, in all circumstances. Even if we don’t feel like
						He’s for us in our current season, we can place our trust in Him because of His
						faithfulness.
						When it seems like we’re drowning, we must be all the more desperate to
						get a glimpse of His face again. To hear just one sweet word for encouragement,
						a word that is sweeter than honey. To claw our way to the truth, because there
						are many things trying to prevent us from getting to God. In all circumstances, we must SEEK Him
						continually, because He doesn’t change.</p>
			    <p> We must SEEK until we are in His presence. When we are abiding in His love, we
						are able to understand how loved we are. In this moment,
						everything is worth it. And at that point, there is nothing that separates us from the love of God.
						Nothing- in the heavens- or on the Earth will-- we are in His presence. </p>
				  <p> Therefore, brothers and sisters, let us continue to seek. In all times. For the God who is good.</p>
	    	</span>
			</span>
