		<h2> Journey Collection </h2>
		<p> Released March 2016 </p>
		<p> JOURNEY is of special significance to us as a team because it’s an intimate
		representation of what we each struggle with in our daily lives. Sometimes
		we get lost in the monotony of our studies and work; other times we find
		ourselves drowning in exhaustion and in our own imperfection. JOURNEY
		represents God’s grace; when we struggle, He has enabled His beloved to
		approach him boldly and to find endurance, joy, and strength through prayer. </p>
		<div class="col-md-12">
			<div class="row design-row">
				<div class="col-md-3">
					<img id=" identity-img" class="img-responsive left-block" src="https://yhwhapparel.files.wordpress.com/2017/04/identity.png"/>
				</div>
				<div class="col-md-9">
					<h4> Identity Coach's Jacket </h4>
					<p> We say we’re athletes, artists, students. We identify ourselves by
						personality type, and pride ourselves in being perceived as polite,
						good looking, or well-liked. We tell the world we go to this college, or
						we’re dating that person; We say, “Look at where I've been. Look at what
						I've done, and who I’ll surely become. This is who I am.” </p>
					<p> But at the core of it all, who are we really? </p>
					<p> When we grow up, and find ourselves without the comfort of our parents.
						When our brains can no longer function at the same level of creativity,
						when the things that once excited us begin to dull. When suddenly our
						personality or friends or circumstances are no longer the same as they once were.</p>
					<p> When there is nothing left of ourselves that we can say or boast of. </p>
					<p> Know what you are. Know who you are. Know Whose you are.
						You are defined by the Maker. </p>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="row design-row">
				<div class="col-md-3">
					<img id="lion-img" class="img-responsive left-block" src="https://yhwhapparel.files.wordpress.com/2017/04/lion.png"/>
				</div>
				<div class="col-md-9">
					<h4> Lion T-Shirt </h4>
					<p> Beautiful, majestic King. He rules with grace, even when we cannot
						fathom the depths of His grace. </p>
					<p> He is powerful and strong. When He roars, the Earth trembles at His might.</p>
					<p> He is gentle. His heart longs for intimacy with His people. </p>
					<p> He is the Lion of Judah, whose kingship was demonstrated
						through His conquering of sin and death at the cross. He is the Lamb
						who was slain, so that we may spend eternity with Him. He gives boldness
						to those who believe in Him, that they may have courage to overcome,
						saying “Fear not, for I am with you.” He has created a kingdom, and has called us
						to be co-heirs with Christ. He is the King of Glory, worthy to be praised.
						Holy, righteous, and bold. </p>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="row design-row">
				<div class="col-md-3">
					<img id="mountain-img" class="responsive left-block" src="https://yhwhapparel.files.wordpress.com/2017/04/mountain.png"/>
				</div>
				<div class="col-md-9">
					<h4> Mountains Baseball Cap </h4>
					<p> Mountains are often associated with sheer might--the idea that if only
					we had enough power, we could move huge obstacles. When we face trials
					that seem to exceed our strengths, let us instead surrender our
					inabilities at the feet of our Father, whose strength is made perfect
					in our weakness. From a distance, our daunting challenges seem unshakeable,
					but when we patiently put our trust in God and approach with His full confidence,
					we will begin to see how far He has moved our mountains. </p>
